“Odds ratio” in Table 3 representsthe ratio between the
probability of a project being a “risky project” and the probability
of it being a “no problem” project(that is, not risky) when the
value of the explanatory variable increases by one unit.
Intuitively speaking, it represents the impact of the explanatory
variable in causing projects to be risky.</p>
      <p>We then investigated the significance and goodness-of-fit of
the whole model. First, the hypothesis HO: bl = b:! = 0 was
tested by the likelihood ratio test. Table 4 showed that the
